<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787C70A5C06373AEF5" bold="true" box="[609,637,482,508]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">—</emphasis>
This name was originally published by 
<bibRefCitation id="22644B78FFA4E5787A36A5C065DEAEF5" author="Halacsy, E. de" box="[1063,1232,482,508]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" refId="ref9719" refString="Halacsy, E. de (1904) Conspectus Florae Graecae, vol. 3. Guilelmi Engelmann, Lispiae, 519 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 9919" type="book" year="1904">Halácsy (1904)</bibRefCitation>
by a short diagnosis (“Palea inferioris setae brevissimae, ejus arista palae quartam partem aequans”). 
<bibRefCitation id="22644B78FFA4E5787A34A62465DDAD29" author="Halacsy, E. de" box="[1061,1235,518,544]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" refId="ref9719" refString="Halacsy, E. de (1904) Conspectus Florae Graecae, vol. 3. Guilelmi Engelmann, Lispiae, 519 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 9919" type="book" year="1904">Halácsy (1904)</bibRefCitation>
listed some places where this taxon was collected (all collectors were mentioned). According to Art. 9.6 of the ICN, all the specimens referring to 
<taxonomicName id="81F54D0AFFA4E5787F1DA66C6361AD61" authorityName="Hackel ex Halacsy" authorityYear="1904" box="[268,623,590,617]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sesleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="nitida" variety="brevidentata">
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787F1DA66C60A3AD61" box="[268,429,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">Sesleria nitida</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787FF3A66C6361AD61" box="[482,623,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">brevidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cited by 
<bibRefCitation id="22644B78FFA4E5787CC2A66C6270AD61" author="Halacsy, E. de" box="[723,894,590,616]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" refId="ref9719" refString="Halacsy, E. de (1904) Conspectus Florae Graecae, vol. 3. Guilelmi Engelmann, Lispiae, 519 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 9919" type="book" year="1904">Halácsy (1904)</bibRefCitation>
are 
<typeStatus id="994E882BFFA4E5787DBDA66D651CAD60" box="[940,1042,591,617]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">syntypes</typeStatus>
. We found at WU (barcode 0079488, image available at http://herbarium.univie.ac.at/database/detail.php?ID=560397), a specimen consisting of two parts that probably belong to the same plant. The original label reported the following note: “ 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787A6BA6B46339ADDD" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">
<taxonomicName id="81F54D0AFFA4E5787A6BA6B46477ADB8" authority="Savi" authorityName="Savi" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Savi" baseAuthorityYear="1800" box="[1146,1401,662,689]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sesleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="argentea" status="var. nova">Sesleria argentea Savi</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="6FB257E0FFA4E5787B93A6B561B0ADDD" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" rank="variety">var. nova</taxonomicNameLabel>
brevidentata Hackel in litt. 1896
</emphasis>
| In Graecia septentrionali: 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787D62A6996533ADDC" box="[883,1085,699,725]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">M. Korax Aetoiae</emphasis>
| 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787A42A6996400ADDD" box="[1107,1294,699,725]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">Tuntas &amp; Leonis</emphasis>
| 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787B35A6996496ADDD" box="[1316,1432,698,725]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">
<date id="324B1049FFA4E5787B35A6996496ADDD" box="[1316,1432,698,725]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" value="1896-08">Aug. 1896</date>
</emphasis>
”. Both locality (“ 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787F2AA6FD6301ADF1" box="[315,527,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">M. Korax Aetoliae</emphasis>
”) and collector (“ 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787CF3A6FD6223ADF1" box="[738,813,735,760]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">Tuntas</emphasis>
”) were quoted by 
<bibRefCitation id="22644B78FFA4E5787A16A6FC65B9ADF1" author="Halacsy, E. de" box="[1031,1207,734,760]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" refId="ref9719" refString="Halacsy, E. de (1904) Conspectus Florae Graecae, vol. 3. Guilelmi Engelmann, Lispiae, 519 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 9919" type="book" year="1904">Halácsy (1904)</bibRefCitation>
, so that WU0079488 specimen is to be considered part of the original material for the name in issue. Accordingly, we here designate WU0079488 specimen as the 
<typeStatus id="994E882BFFA4E5787FC3A7046337AC49" box="[466,569,806,832]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">lectotype</typeStatus>
of the name 
<taxonomicName id="81F54D0AFFA4E5787CD7A70562ECAC49" authorityName="Hackel ex Halacsy" authorityYear="1904" box="[710,994,806,833]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sesleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="nitida" variety="brevidentata">
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787CD7A705622FAC49" box="[710,801,806,833]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">S. nitida</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787D47A70462ECAC49" box="[854,994,806,832]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">brevidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To be noted that three revision labels are affixed on the 
<typeStatus id="994E882BFFA4E5787F36A7686080AC6D" box="[295,398,842,868]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">lectotype</typeStatus>
sheet. On one of them, the word “ 
<typeStatus id="994E882BFFA4E5787D17A7686274AC6D" box="[774,890,842,868]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">holotypus</typeStatus>
” is reported together with a reference to the author and the date of typification (“typificavit L. Sonnleitner WU 
<date id="324B1049FFA4E5787D37A74C62A7AC80" box="[806,937,878,905]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" value="2015-01-13">2015-01-13</date>
”). However, since several 
<typeStatus id="994E882BFFA4E5787ADEA74D643FAC80" box="[1231,1329,879,905]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">syntypes</typeStatus>
were cited in the protologue, a 
<typeStatus id="994E882BFFA4E5787F64A7B060D9ACA5" box="[373,471,914,940]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">holotype</typeStatus>
cannot be established, whereas a lectotypification is allowed (Arts. 9.1, 9.2, and 9.5 of the ICN). All three revision labels classify the 
<typeStatus id="994E882BFFA4E5787CABA794622FACD9" box="[698,801,950,976]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">lectotype</typeStatus>
as 
<taxonomicName id="81F54D0AFFA4E5787D59A79565D6ACD9" authority="Boissier &amp; Orphanides" authorityName="Boissier &amp; Orphanides" box="[840,1240,950,977]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sesleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vaginalis">
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787D59A79562C3ACD9" box="[840,973,950,977]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">S. vaginalis</emphasis>
Boissier &amp; Orphanides
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="22644B78FFA4E5787AEFA79461B1ACFD" author="Boissier, P. E." pageId="10" pageNumber="99" refId="ref8987" refString="Boissier, P. E. (1859) Diagnoses plantarum orientalium novarum, ser. 2, vol. 4. Herrmann, Leipzig, 146 pp." type="book" year="1859">Boissier (1859: 130)</bibRefCitation>
. According to the current species concept in 
<taxonomicName id="81F54D0AFFA4E5787CD5A7F862BFACFC" authority="(Deyl 1946)" baseAuthorityName="Deyl" baseAuthorityYear="1946" box="[708,945,986,1013]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sesleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787CD5A7F86210ACFD" box="[708,798,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">Sesleria</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="22644B78FFA4E5787D3EA7F862A7ACFC" author="Deyl, M." box="[815,937,986,1013]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 256" refId="ref9121" refString="Deyl, M. (1946) Study of the genus Sesleria. Opera Botanika Cechica 3: 1 - 256." type="journal article" year="1946">Deyl 1946</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
we agree this identification and classify the specimen WU0079488 as 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787FBBA7DD633CAB11" box="[426,562,1022,1049]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">
<taxonomicName id="81F54D0AFFA4E5787FBBA7DD6320AB11" box="[426,558,1022,1049]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sesleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vaginalis">S. vaginalis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
whose occurrence on Mt. Korax (highest peak of the Vardousia massif in central Greece, and locus classicus of 
<taxonomicName id="81F54D0AFFA4E5787FF2A001620BAB35" authorityName="Hackel ex Halacsy" authorityYear="1904" box="[483,773,1058,1085]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sesleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="nitida" variety="brevidentata">
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787FF2A001634FAB35" box="[483,577,1058,1085]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">S. nitida</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787C68A000620BAB35" box="[633,773,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">brevidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is confirmed by several authors (
<bibRefCitation id="22644B78FFA4E5787A99A000640DAB35" author="Strid, A." box="[1160,1283,1058,1084]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" refId="ref11143" refString="Strid, A. (Ed.) (1986) Mountain flora of Greece, vol. 1. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, 852 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2807396" type="book" year="1986">Strid 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="22644B78FFA4E5787B1FA0006072AB69" author="Dimitrellos, G. &amp; Christodoulakis, D." pageId="10" pageNumber="99" pagination="215 - 229" refId="ref9143" refString="Dimitrellos, G. &amp; Christodoulakis, D. (1999) The phytogeographical distribution patterns of the flora of Mt Tirnfristos (N. W. Sterea ElIas, Greece). Flora mediterranea 9: 215 - 229." type="journal article" year="1999">Dimitrellos &amp; Christodoulakis 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="22644B78FFA4E5787F98A0646393AB69" author="Kuzmanovic, N. &amp; Lakusic, D. &amp; Frajman, B. &amp; Alegro, A. &amp; Schonswetter, P." box="[393,669,1094,1120]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" pagination="1349 - 1370" refId="ref10241" refString="Kuzmanovic, N., Lakusic, D., Frajman, B., Alegro, A. &amp; Schonswetter, P. (2017) Phylogenetic relationships in Seslerieae (Poaceae) including resurrection of Psilathera and Sesleriella, two monotypic genera endemic to the Alps. Taxon 66: 1349 - 1370. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 666.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Kuzmanović 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787C0EA0656356AB69" box="[543,600,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). Accordingly, any possible reference of 
<taxonomicName id="81F54D0AFFA4E5787A78A0656483AB69" authorityName="Hackel ex Halacsy" authorityYear="1904" box="[1129,1421,1094,1121]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sesleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="nitida" variety="brevidentata">
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787A78A06565C9AB69" box="[1129,1223,1094,1121]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">S. nitida</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787B11A0646483AB69" box="[1280,1421,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">brevidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as belonging to the group of 
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787FB6A0496304AB8D" box="[423,522,1130,1157]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">
<taxonomicName id="81F54D0AFFA4E5787FB6A0496308AB8D" authorityName="Ten. Pampanini" authorityYear="1927" box="[423,518,1130,1157]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sesleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nitida">S. nitida</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
as assumed by 
<bibRefCitation id="22644B78FFA4E5787CA7A048626DAB8D" author="Halacsy, E. de" box="[694,867,1130,1156]" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" refId="ref9719" refString="Halacsy, E. de (1904) Conspectus Florae Graecae, vol. 3. Guilelmi Engelmann, Lispiae, 519 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 9919" type="book" year="1904">Halácsy (1904)</bibRefCitation>
, must be excluded, 
<taxonomicName id="81F54D0AFFA4E5787A2CA0496597AB8D" authorityName="Ten. Pampanini" authorityYear="1927" box="[1085,1177,1130,1157]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sesleria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nitida">
<emphasis id="7481EA9BFFA4E5787A2CA0496597AB8D" box="[1085,1177,1130,1157]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">S. nitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being a species endemic to the central-southern Apennines (peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="3EE27619FFA4E5787C9CA0AC63CBABA0" box="[653,709,1166,1193]" name="Italy" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">Italy</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
